        <p class="card-body">
          The goal is to narrow the gap, especially for traditional Paper, Bukkit, and Spigot assumptions.
          When SilkMC can safely bridge behavior, it does. When a plugin crosses unsafe thread boundaries,
          SilkMC should disable it cleanly and tell you why instead of taking the server down with it.
        </p>
        <span class="card-chip blue">compatibility over guesswork</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

