        <div class="card-feat-inner">
          <div class="card-feat-left">
            <span class="card-icon">S</span>
            <div class="card-title">Scheduler compatibility bridges</div>
            <p class="card-body">
              SilkMC keeps Folia's regional multithreaded model, but bridges more legacy scheduler behavior where it
              can be done safely. That helps older Paper and Bukkit plugins get further without immediately exploding.
            </p>
            <span class="card-chip">safer legacy task handling</span>
          </div>
          <div class="card-metric-box">
            <span class="card-metric-num">Paper</span>
            <span class="card-metric-sub">first-class compatibility target</span>
